1 olive oil
2 potato
1 Brown Onion
1 tsp balsamic vinegar
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet beef strips
2 Wholemeal Panini
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
½ pear
1 sachet Italian Herbs

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut
potato into fries, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss
to coat. Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Help out by tossing the fries with the
olive oil and salt.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice onion and pear
(see ingredients).

Little cooks: Don your goggles and have a go at
peeling off the onion's outer layer!

• In large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook onion, stirring,
until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Add the balsamic
vinegar, the brown sugar and a splash of water,
then mix well. Cook until dark and sticky,
3-5 minutes.
• Transfer to a small bowl.

• When the fries have 5 minutes remaining,
combine Italian herbs, a good pinch of salt
and pepper and a drizzle of olive oil in medium
bowl. Add beef strips, tossing to coat.
• Wash and dry the frying pan, then return to high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches until
browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Help toss the beef in the seasoning.
Make sure to wash your hands well afterwards!

• Meanwhile, place wholemeal panini directly on
a wire rack in the oven.
• Bake until heated through, 5 minutes.

• Slice each panini in half, then spread with
creamy pesto dressing.
• Top with beef, caramelised onion, pear and
spinach & rocket mix.
• Serve with fries. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the
paninis!